
machine		= decides which preconfigured host it will run as (SLU specific)
inet.routes	= static route options
dummy0.nic	= dummy network interface
eth*.nic	= Ethernet network interface(s)
ntp		= NTP time server (also edit /etc/ntp.conf)

The SLU specific option "machine" can be either empty (default) or contain the line:

export MACHINE=hades
or
export MACHINE=expgw

for example...

